50|$|Wang {{began his}} career at LC in 1956 {{to work on a}} {{microfilm}} project. In 1958, he became a cataloguer in the newly established Far Eastern Languages Section where he was asked to head up an innovative project to use a <b>photocomposing</b> <b>machine</b> that the Library just purchased from Japan to produce catalog cards with CJK (Chinese, Japanese and Korean) scripts, which put the practice of hand-copying CJK characters to cards to an end: quite a technological breakthrough at the time.|$|E

